  "_README": [
    "Phase 2 address table for generate-phase2-peer-batches.ts.",
    "",
    "PURPOSE: re-wire the LayerZero V2 CREATE_TOKEN peer mesh after redeploying the",
    "dispatchers. Each dispatcher must setPeer(eid, bytes32(peer)) for every OTHER",
    "chain's dispatcher. V2 mesh = all 19 chains below (19*18 = 342 wires). V3 mesh =",
    "ONLY arbitrum/base/polygon (the 3 chains with a CreateTokenDispatcherV3) among",
    "themselves (3*2 = 6 wires). The two meshes are wired SEPARATELY, never mixed.",
    "",
    "HOW TO USE:",
    "  1. cp phase2-addresses.template.json phase2-addresses.json",
    "  2. Redeploy the dispatcher(s) per chain (scripts/deploy-create-token-dispatcher.ts",
    "     for V2, deploy-create-token-dispatcher-v3.ts for the 3 V3 chains).",
    "  3. Fill 'newDispatcher' (the new V2 CreateTokenDispatcher just deployed) for every",
    "     chain, and 'newDispatcherV3' for arbitrum/base/polygon.",
    "  4. Run: npx ts-node scripts/safe/generate-phase2-peer-batches.ts",
    "     (reads phase2-addresses.json; falls back to this template if absent).",
    "",
    "Chains with a blank/zero 'newDispatcher' are SKIPPED in the V2 mesh, and chains",
    "with a blank/zero 'newDispatcherV3' are simply not part of the V3 mesh — so you",
    "can generate a partial set and wire in waves as chains come online.",
    "",
    "'eid' is from lib/constants/gatewayChains.ts (source of truth, cross-checked against",
    "scripts/generatePeerWiringBatches.ts CHAIN_EIDS). 'safe' is from",
    "scripts/safe/phase1-addresses.template.json (per-chain Safe owner). Verify both",
    "before signing. Cronos (25) is excluded: no LZ V2 endpoint. Ethereum (1) is not a",
    "live dispatcher chain and is excluded."
